import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Cylinders'], data['Horsepower'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Cylinders and Horsepower?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Miles_per_Gallon'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of Miles_per_Gallon over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
